body:
yitzle wrote:
> What would be the 'correct' way to deal with a function that takes eg
> 2 scalars and an array?
> 
> Something like this?
> 
> sub mySub($$@) {
>  my $first = shift;
>  my $last = shift;
>  my @list = @_;
>  ....
> }
> 
> or
> 
> sub mySub($$@) {
>  my $first = $_[0];
>  my $last = $_[1];
>  my @list = @_[2.. (scalar @_ - 1)];
>  ....
> }
> 
> or

sub mySub {
    my ( $first, $last, @list ) = @_;
    ....
    }




John
